root: ^That's all there is to it! This is the last part inside of the case!
^As mentioned before, it is vitally important that your computer has proper cooling. Or else you risk breaking many parts in your computer!
^Most standard fans will do the job well though, and when purchasing a heat sink, you just have to make sure it's compatible with your CPU. Otherwise, it might not fit correctly.
^Now that the inside of the computer is complete, let's move on to the stuff outside the computer!
